# **Section Five: The Quick Leadership Assessment, the First Build**

The free, five-minute front door, and the first thing to code. It scores out of 60 across the four signature leader stories (Origin, Vision, Values, Transformation) and the behavioral and impact items, and closes with the one question you read yourself: if every title and credential were stripped away, what story would you tell about who you are and why you do this work.

| **SCORE / 60** | **ZONE** | **WHAT THE RESULT PAGE LEADS WITH** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **0 to 19** | **Story At Risk** | Leading on credentials and data. The gap is costing influence now. |
| **20 to 31** | **Story Emerging** | Defaults to the Police Report under pressure. Aware, but fragile. |
| **32 to 41** | **Story Drift** | Go-to stories that work, but no consistent spine. |
| **42 to 51** | **Story Developing** | Real strengths, ready to codify the full range and deploy it. |
| **52 to 60** | **Story Aligned** | Already using story as a leadership tool. The work is building it in others. |

Result flow: score, then zone, then a result page with the zone video and worksheet, then the Kit email sequence, then the anchor-plus-product call to action. The band writes the message. The qualifier sets the rung. The anchor flexes to fit the reader.

# **Section Six: Build Notes for Claude Code and Netlify**

- One embeddable component, shared across both sites, in the pattern of the CultureCon webinar flow, so a visitor gets the same instrument and result wherever they start.

- Capture email, the one open question you read yourself, and a light qualifier (role or title, organization size, timeframe). Never a budget field.

- Score by summing to a total, then threshold into one of the five tiers. Keep thresholds in a config file so you can tune them with real data without a rebuild.

- Store three things separately: tier, objective, and inferred capacity. Tier and objective set the work; capacity sets the rung; keeping them apart is what lets the band stay independent of funds.

- On result: route to the zone result page, apply Kit tags (one shared completed tag plus one zone tag), trigger the zone email sequence, and surface the anchor-plus-product offer.

- The six teasers are lightweight versions of the same logic. Each ends with a link to its mapped instrument. Build the free Quick Leadership Assessment first; the rest reuse the pattern.

# **Section Seven: Confirmed, and the Few Still Open**

**Confirmed and locked: **five zones canonical; the 60-point thresholds above; the anchor-plus-product pairing with a flexible anchor; Personal Narrative kept and Personal Life retired; band decoupled from funds; qualify by inference.

Still open, and small:

- The condensed go-between book: its title and one-line positioning, so it can take its place on the anchor ladder.

- Dedicated landing-page URLs per instrument, so each teaser wires to its own page instead of the shared drrodberger.com door.

- Whether to relabel the teasers' three coarse bands to the five-zone language now, or leave them coarse and route by tier underneath.

**One question before the build.**

The teasers are the only thing most people will ever meet, because they live where the scrolling happens. If a stranger reads one teaser and nothing else, does it leave them with a result worth keeping and a single clear next step, or does it leave them admiring the question and forgetting the door?

*Yours in Narrative.*